KRS 11A.211 and 11A.216 do not apply to efforts to influence executive agency decisions or conduct executive agency lobbying activity by any of the following:
Appearances at public hearings of the committees or interim committees of the General Assembly, at court proceedings, at rule-making or adjudication proceedings, or at other public meetings;
News, editorial, and advertising statements published in newspapers, journals, or magazines, or broadcast over radio or television;
The gathering and furnishing of information and news by bona fide reporters, correspondents, or news bureaus to news media described in subsection (1)(b) of this section; or
Publications primarily designed for and distributed to members of associations or charitable or fraternal nonprofit corporations.
